T1  - Identification in Nonparametric Simultaneous Equations Models
AU  - Matzkin, Rosa L.
Y1  - 2008/09/01
PY  - 2008
DA  - 2008/09/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA5940
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 945
EP  - 978
VL  - 76
IS  - 5
KW  - Nonparametric methods
KW  - nonadditive models
KW  - nonseparable models
KW  - identification
KW  - simultaneous equations
KW  - endogeneity
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA5940
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - This paper provides conditions for identification of functionals in nonparametric simultaneous equations models with nonadditive unobservable random terms. The conditions are derived from a characterization of observational equivalence between models. We show that, in the models considered, observational equivalence can be characterized by a restriction on the rank of a matrix. The use of the new results is exemplified by deriving previously known results about identification in parametric and nonparametric models as well as new results. A stylized method for analyzing identification, which is useful in some situations, is also presented.
ER  - 

