UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA6175
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Rabin (2000) proved that a low level of risk aversion with respect to small gambles leads to a high, and absurd, level of risk aversion with respect to large gambles. Rabin's arguments strongly depend on expected utility theory, but we show that similar arguments apply to general non-expected utility theories.
ER  - 

